    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>The Battle of the Sexes example is from Nordstrom's textbook. The shift from zero-sum to non-zero-sum is not just a change in payoff numbers. It's a change in the strategic structure: communication, cooperation, and multiple equilibria all become relevant. This is why Chapters 2-3 (zero-sum) needed different tools from Chapter 4 onward.</p>

